{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Vi9Pk7eqJCRdaZHYgCpdJ1","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# 0.7.0 PERF-VECTOR-QUANT — implementation handoff\n2\t\n3\tDrafted: 2026-05-27\n4\tType: **Implementation handoff** — TDD-disciplined slice work\n5\tacross 2 packs. ADR drafting comes first; then Pack 1; then\n6\tPack 2.\n7\t\n8\t## What you are shipping\n9\t\n10\tBinary-quantization (`bit[768]`) with f32 rerank on the existing\n11\t`sqlite-vec` extension, plus a metadata+partition_key schema\n12\tmigration. Closes AC-013 (currently p50=2048 ms / p99=2327 ms at\n13\tcanonical-CI N=1M) to within the proposed 80 / 300 ms budget by\n14\t~20× reduction in per-query bytes-scanned.\n15\t\n16\tThe research that grounds this work:\n17\t`dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md` (HITL-RESPONDED).\n18\tRead it first. The HITL doc\n19\t`dev/plans/0.7.0-HITL-recommendations.md` is the authoritative\n20\trecord of decisions.\n21\t\n22\t## Hard constraints carried forward\n23\t\n24\t- **Canonical CI is the only honored signal for verdict\n25\t  purposes** (perf-experiments hard constraint).\n26\t- **TDD discipline**: every behavior-change lands with a RED\n27\t  test first. The recall-floor test and the re-pinned AC-013\n28\t  latency test must FAIL at canonical-CI scale before Pack 2's\n29\t  query-path change.\n30\t- **`SQLITE_CONFIG_PCACHE2` is the architectural lever for 0.7.0.**\n31\t  This binary-quant + rerank work is a **data-encoding change**,\n32\t  not a second architectural lever — see the architectural-lever\n33\t  accounting in `dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md`. If a\n34\t  reviewer disagrees, fallback is to ship Pack 1 only in 0.7.0\n35\t  and slip Pack 2 to 0.7.1.\n36\t- **No push to origin without explicit user OK.**\n37\t- **No ADR lock-flip without HITL sign-off.**\n38\t- **Single-writer + projection-cursor freshness contracts**\n39\t  (`crates/fathomdb-engine/src/database_lock.rs`,\n40\t   `crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs` writer loop) must be\n41\t  preserved. Double-write of the bit column happens inside the\n42\t  same writer transaction that inserts the f32 row.\n43\t- **`EmbedderIdentity` contract is unchanged.** Do NOT switch\n44\t  the embedder. The existing `VaryingEmbedder` /\n45\t  embedder-profile pinning at `lib.rs:3248-3260` stays.\n46\t\n47\t## Read first (in order)\n48\t\n49\t1. `dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md` — load-bearing\n50\t   plan; Pack 1/2 split, HITL locks, technique citations.\n51\t2. `dev/plans/0.7.0-HITL-recommendations.md` — HITL decision\n52\t   record (PCACHE2 stack + this vector-cost work).\n53\t3. `dev/plans/runs/0.7.0-PERF-EXP-W4.1-ac013-canonical-output.json`\n54\t   — the canonical-CI measurement that drove the work.\n55\t4. `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs`:\n56\t   - **`register_sqlite_vec_extension`** (~line 3107) — extension registration; bit[N] is already available via sqlite-vec 0.1.7.\n57\t   - **`read_search_in_tx`** (~line 2317-2323) — the hot\n58\t     query you're rewriting in Pack 2.\n59\t   - **`_fathomdb_vector_rows` writer insert** (~line 2846)\n60\t     — the ingest site you're double-writing at in Pack 1.\n61\t   - **`vector_default` CREATE VIRTUAL TABLE** (~line\n62\t     3278-3283) — schema you're migrating in Pack 1.\n63\t   - **`_fathomdb_embedder_profiles`** (~line 3248-3260) —\n64\t     embedder identity / profile pinning. Leave alone.\n65\t   - Writer loop pins: lines 2174, 2242, 2846.\n66\t5. `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates.rs`:\n67\t   - `ac_013_vector_retrieval_latency` (~line 487).\n68\t   - `ac_019_mixed_retrieval_stress_workload_tail` (~line 609).\n69\t   - `seed_ac013_corpus` + `ac013_query_bodies` for the fixture.\n70\t   - `AC013_BUDGET_*` constants at lines 149-150.\n71\t6. `crates/fathomdb-engine/Cargo.toml` — confirm\n72\t   `sqlite-vec = \"=0.1.7\"` pin. Pack 1 may optionally bump to\n73\t   `0.1.9` for the constraint-column improvements — only if\n74\t   needed; not required for `bit[N]`.\n75\t\n76\t## Step 0 — Draft the ADR\n77\t\n78\tBefore Pack 1 lands a single byte of code, draft an ADR:\n79\t\n80\t`dev/adr/ADR-0.7.0-vector-binary-quant.md` (or rename the\n81\texisting `ADR-0.7.0-text-query-latency-gates-revised.md` if it\n82\tmakes more sense to bundle).\n83\t\n84\tThe ADR must cover:\n85\t\n86\t- Problem (AC-013 canonical-CI gap, root cause).\n87\t- Decision: binary quantization + f32 rerank on `sqlite-vec`\n88\t  0.1.7; metadata + partition_key on the same migration.\n89\t- Alternatives considered (vectorlite, sqlite-vec ANN alpha,\n90\t  Rust-side `usearch`, embedder change) — all rejected, with\n91\t  reasons from the research doc.\n92\t- Consequences: schema change, ingest cost, query-path\n93\t  rewrite, recall floor as RED test, post-0.7.0 follow-ups.\n94\t- Status: `draft, HITL-required` initially. Lock-flip is\n95\t  orchestrator's; do not flip prematurely.\n96\t\n97\t## Pack 1 — schema migration + ingest double-write\n98\t\n99\tGoal: land the new schema and the new ingest path. **No reader\n100\tbehavior change.** AC-013 / AC-019 still measure on the\n101\tunindexed f32 path; their numbers stay at 2048/2327 until\n102\tPack 2.\n103\t\n104\t### 1.1 — Schema migration\n105\t\n106\tModify `vector_default` (or add a sibling\n107\t`vector_default_bin`). Decision criterion:\n108\t\n109\t- **Sibling column on the same vec0 table** — simpler\n110\t  application code; sqlite-vec supports mixed `float[768]` +\n111\t  `bit[768]` columns on the same vec0. **Default choice.**\n112\t- **Sibling table** — only if the column-flavour hits a\n113\t  vec0 limitation (e.g., metadata column count limit, which is\n114\t  16 per\n115\t  [sqlite-vec features](https://alexgarcia.xyz/blog/2024/sqlite-vec-metadata-release/index.html)).\n116\t\n117\tNew columns:\n118\t\n119\t- `embedding_bin bit[768]` — the load-bearing quantized\n120\t  column. Built with `vec_quantize_binary(embedding)`.\n121\t- `source_type TEXT` — **partition_key, locked HITL\n122\t  2026-05-27**. Cardinality ~6 (email, article, paper, meeting,\n123\t  note, todo). Maps to user-facing search-scope filters and\n124\t  yields fast pre-filtered KNN under `WHERE source_type = ?`.\n125\t  Existing chunk records have a vector kind via\n126\t  `_fathomdb_vector_rows.kind` (verify exact column name when\n127\t  reading lib.rs); map kind → source_type at write time\n128\t  (deterministic 1:1 mapping for current kinds; the\n129\t  source_type vocabulary is the authoritative set going\n130\t  forward).\n131\t- Additional metadata columns (non-partition): `kind` (kept\n132\t  for backwards compat if it differs from source_type),\n133\t  `created_at`, `tags`, `project_mentions`, etc. Per HITL\n134\t  Q5: descriptive retrieval filters go in metadata columns +\n135\t  WHERE predicates, not partition_keys. vec0 metadata column\n136\t  limit is 16; budget the schema with headroom.\n137\t\n138\tMigration SQL: one-pass `INSERT ... SELECT\n139\tvec_quantize_binary(embedding) FROM vector_default` for the\n140\texisting 1 M test corpus. Costs ~64 s on the dev box; well\n141\tinside the workflow timeout.\n142\t\n143\t### 1.2 — Writer ingest double-write\n144\t\n145\tAt `_fathomdb_vector_rows` insert site (`lib.rs:2846` area):\n146\t\n147\t- After the f32 `embedding` insert, compute\n148\t  `vec_quantize_binary(embedding)` and insert into the\n149\t  `embedding_bin` column in the same transaction.\n150\t- The bit column is non-nullable post-Pack 1 (every f32 row\n151\t  has a bit row); enforce via NOT NULL or by post-write\n152\t  migration.\n153\t- Populate `kind` + `partition_key` from the existing chunk\n154\t  record fields.\n155\t- The writer transaction commits all columns atomically — no\n156\t  separate commit for the bit column.\n157\t\n158\t### 1.3 — Pack 1 tests\n159\t\n160\t- **Migration round-trip test** — insert a known f32 vector,\n161\t  verify the bit column contains the expected popcount\n162\t  pattern (`vec_distance_hamming` returns 0 against itself\n163\t  after binarization).\n164\t- **Writer regression** — existing AC-012, AC-017, AC-018,\n165\t  AC-020 tests continue to pass. Pack 1 changes schema but\n166\t  not query semantics, so all should be GREEN.\n167\t- **No AC-013 budget change yet** — AC-013 stays pinned at\n168\t  the unindexed 50/200 budget (current `perf_gates.rs:149-150`)\n169\t  and continues to fail at canonical-CI 1M scale until\n170\t  Pack 2.\n171\t\n172\t### 1.4 — Pack 1 closure\n173\t\n174\tLand the schema + ingest changes as one or two commits on\n175\t`main` (campaign convention from PCACHE2). No canonical-CI\n176\tdispatch is required for Pack 1 — the schema change has no\n177\tRED gate at canonical scale. Smoke test via dev-box AC-013 at\n178\tN=10_000 to confirm the ingest double-write doesn't crash.\n179\t\n180\t## Pack 2 — query-path swap + RED tests\n181\t\n182\tGoal: switch the reader to bit-KNN → f32 rerank and pin the\n183\tnew AC-013 budgets.\n184\t\n185\t### 2.1 — RED tests FIRST\n186\t\n187\tBefore the query rewrite, land:\n188\t\n189\t- **AC-013 latency budget re-pin** in\n190\t  `tests/perf_gates.rs:149-150`:\n191\t  - `AC013_BUDGET_P50 = Duration::from_millis(80);`\n192\t  - `AC013_BUDGET_P99 = Duration::from_millis(300);`\n193\t- **New AC recall-floor test** (e.g., `ac_NNN_recall_at_10`):\n194\t  - Computes brute-force f32 ground truth at test-setup\n195\t    (one pass through the existing f32 column, no\n196\t    rerank).\n197\t  - Runs the production search path, captures top-10 IDs\n198\t    per query.\n199\t  - Asserts `recall@10 ≥ 0.90` (HITL-locked floor).\n200\t  - The ground-truth pass uses the *same* f32 column that\n201\t    Pack 2 retains for rerank — single corpus, both jobs.\n202\t\n203\tBoth tests must FAIL at canonical-CI N=1M before the query\n204\trewrite lands. Dispatch the perf-canonical workflow with\n205\t`targets=\"ac013 ac019\"` and the locked W4.1-stacked-O1 env\n206\tknobs (see HITL doc) to confirm RED.\n207\t\n208\t### 2.2 — `read_search_in_tx` rewrite\n209\t\n210\tAt `lib.rs:2317-2323`, replace the single-phase f32 KNN with\n211\ttwo-phase:\n212\t\n213\t```sql\n214\t-- Phase 1: bit-KNN to top-K candidates (K=64 default)\n215\tWITH candidates AS (\n216\t  SELECT rowid, distance AS bit_distance\n217\t  FROM vector_default\n218\t  WHERE embedding_bin MATCH vec_quantize_binary(vec_f32(?1))\n219\t  ORDER BY distance\n220\t  LIMIT 64\n221\t)\n222\t-- Phase 2: f32 rerank on the candidate set\n223\tSELECT c.rowid, vec_distance_l2(v.embedding, vec_f32(?1)) AS d\n224\tFROM candidates c\n225\tJOIN vector_default v USING (rowid)\n226\tORDER BY d\n227\tLIMIT 10\n228\t```\n229\t\n230\t(Exact SQL TBD against sqlite-vec syntax — see\n231\t[sqlite-vec API ref](https://deepwiki.com/asg017/sqlite-vec/3-api-reference)\n232\tand the binary-quant guide cited in the research doc.)\n233\t\n234\tK=64 picked from the binary-quant literature (Cohere, Kyle\n235\tHowells benches) for ≥ 95 % recall@10 at our scale. Make K a\n236\tconstant / config knob so future tuning is cheap.\n237\t\n238\t### 2.3 — Pack 2 validation\n239\t\n240\t- Local dev-box smoke at N=10_000 — both tests pass.\n241\t- Canonical-CI dispatch with the same lever stack:\n242\t  - AC-013 GREEN at ≤ 80 / 300 ms.\n243\t  - AC-019 GREEN (existing 10× bound; should improve\n244\t    substantially).\n245\t  - Recall@10 ≥ 0.90 against f32 ground truth.\n246\t\n247\t### 2.4 — Pack 2 closure\n248\t\n249\tOnce canonical-CI is GREEN, the AC-013 / AC-019 rows in the\n250\trevised-budgets ADR can be filled with the measurement\n251\tnumbers + headroom (~10 %), and the ADR lock-flip can\n252\tproceed.\n253\t\n254\t## Done = ?\n255\t\n256\tThis handoff closes when:\n257\t\n258\t- ADR drafted (`status: draft, HITL-required`).\n259\t- Pack 1 lands; ingest double-writes; schema migration\n260\t  documented in the ADR.\n261\t- Pack 2 lands; both RED tests transition to GREEN at\n262\t  canonical-CI; recall@10 ≥ 0.90.\n263\t- HITL signs off on the AC-013 / AC-019 numeric budgets.\n264\t- ADR `status: locked`; orchestrator commits the lock-flip.\n265\t- `dev/notes/pcache2-followups.md` is updated to reference\n266\t  this work as the AC-013/019 closure.\n267\t- Per-slice closure JSONs land in `dev/plans/runs/`.\n268\t\n269\t## Out of scope\n270\t\n271\t- Vectorlite, sqlite-vec ANN alpha, usearch / instant-distance.\n272\t  Tracked for post-0.7.0 in `dev/notes/pcache2-followups.md`.\n273\t- Embedder change.\n274\t- ANN graph index of any kind.\n275\t- Multi-process / multi-DB testing (FathomDB's single-writer\n276\t  contract is preserved as-is).\n277\t- AC-017 / AC-018 changes (out of scope; existing budgets\n278\t  hold).\n279\t\n280\t## Open items the implementing agent should escalate to HITL\n281\t\n282\t- If `vec_quantize_binary()` semantics differ from this\n283\t  handoff's assumption (e.g., it requires normalized input\n284\t  but `VaryingEmbedder` produces unnormalized vectors),\n285\t  escalate before Pack 1 ingest changes.\n286\t- If the metadata-column count (max 16 per vec0) is\n287\t  insufficient for FathomDB's actual kind cardinality + future\n288\t  schema needs, escalate before Pack 1 schema design.\n289\t- If the recall floor at K=64 falls below 0.90 on the AC-013\n290\t  fixture, escalate before Pack 2 GREEN-test commit. K may\n291\t  need to rise to 128 or 256; document the choice.\n292\t- If a future reviewer counts binary-quant as a second\n293\t  architectural lever, escalate immediately — fallback is\n294\t  to slip Pack 2 to 0.7.1.\n295\t\n296\t## Citations\n297\t\n298\t- Research: `dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md`.\n299\t- HITL doc: `dev/plans/0.7.0-HITL-recommendations.md`.\n300\t- PCACHE2 ADR (precedent for HITL-driven 0.7.0 architectural\n301\t  lever): `dev/adr/ADR-0.7.0-ac020-architectural-lever.md`.\n302\t- Budgets ADR (target for the post-Pack-2 lock-flip):\n303\t  `dev/adr/ADR-0.7.0-text-query-latency-gates-revised.md`.\n304\t- sqlite-vec binary quantization guide:\n305\t  https://alexgarcia.xyz/sqlite-vec/guides/binary-quant.html\n306\t- sqlite-vec API reference:\n307\t  https://deepwiki.com/asg017/sqlite-vec/3-api-reference\n308\t- sqlite-vec metadata + partition release:\n309\t  https://alexgarcia.xyz/blog/2024/sqlite-vec-metadata-release/index.html\n310\t- Kyle Howells binary-quant benchmark:\n311\t  https://ikyle.me/blog/2025/binary-quantized-embeddings\n312\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"aa315b5f-03de-4674-91e7-1c237d33c95a","uuid":"b02fb89e-7e94-4843-89bf-89297e2c9fce","timestamp":"2026-05-27T13:11:53.145Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/fdb-0.7.0-PVQ-S0-20260527T130459Z/dev/plans/prompts/0.7.0-PERF-VECTOR-QUANT-HANDOFF.md","content":"# 0.7.0 PERF-VECTOR-QUANT — implementation handoff\n\nDrafted: 2026-05-27\nType: **Implementation handoff** — TDD-disciplined slice work\nacross 2 packs. ADR drafting comes first; then Pack 1; then\nPack 2.\n\n## What you are shipping\n\nBinary-quantization (`bit[768]`) with f32 rerank on the existing\n`sqlite-vec` extension, plus a metadata+partition_key schema\nmigration. Closes AC-013 (currently p50=2048 ms / p99=2327 ms at\ncanonical-CI N=1M) to within the proposed 80 / 300 ms budget by\n~20× reduction in per-query bytes-scanned.\n\nThe research that grounds this work:\n`dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md` (HITL-RESPONDED).\nRead it first. The HITL doc\n`dev/plans/0.7.0-HITL-recommendations.md` is the authoritative\nrecord of decisions.\n\n## Hard constraints carried forward\n\n- **Canonical CI is the only honored signal for verdict\n  purposes** (perf-experiments hard constraint).\n- **TDD discipline**: every behavior-change lands with a RED\n  test first. The recall-floor test and the re-pinned AC-013\n  latency test must FAIL at canonical-CI scale before Pack 2's\n  query-path change.\n- **`SQLITE_CONFIG_PCACHE2` is the architectural lever for 0.7.0.**\n  This binary-quant + rerank work is a **data-encoding change**,\n  not a second architectural lever — see the architectural-lever\n  accounting in `dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md`. If a\n  reviewer disagrees, fallback is to ship Pack 1 only in 0.7.0\n  and slip Pack 2 to 0.7.1.\n- **No push to origin without explicit user OK.**\n- **No ADR lock-flip without HITL sign-off.**\n- **Single-writer + projection-cursor freshness contracts**\n  (`crates/fathomdb-engine/src/database_lock.rs`,\n   `crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs` writer loop) must be\n  preserved. Double-write of the bit column happens inside the\n  same writer transaction that inserts the f32 row.\n- **`EmbedderIdentity` contract is unchanged.** Do NOT switch\n  the embedder. The existing `VaryingEmbedder` /\n  embedder-profile pinning at `lib.rs:3248-3260` stays.\n\n## Read first (in order)\n\n1. `dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md` — load-bearing\n   plan; Pack 1/2 split, HITL locks, technique citations.\n2. `dev/plans/0.7.0-HITL-recommendations.md` — HITL decision\n   record (PCACHE2 stack + this vector-cost work).\n3. `dev/plans/runs/0.7.0-PERF-EXP-W4.1-ac013-canonical-output.json`\n   — the canonical-CI measurement that drove the work.\n4. `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs`:\n   - **`register_sqlite_vec_extension`** (~line 3107) — extension registration; bit[N] is already available via sqlite-vec 0.1.7.\n   - **`read_search_in_tx`** (~line 2317-2323) — the hot\n     query you're rewriting in Pack 2.\n   - **`_fathomdb_vector_rows` writer insert** (~line 2846)\n     — the ingest site you're double-writing at in Pack 1.\n   - **`vector_default` CREATE VIRTUAL TABLE** (~line\n     3278-3283) — schema you're migrating in Pack 1.\n   - **`_fathomdb_embedder_profiles`** (~line 3248-3260) —\n     embedder identity / profile pinning. Leave alone.\n   - Writer loop pins: lines 2174, 2242, 2846.\n5. `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates.rs`:\n   - `ac_013_vector_retrieval_latency` (~line 487).\n   - `ac_019_mixed_retrieval_stress_workload_tail` (~line 609).\n   - `seed_ac013_corpus` + `ac013_query_bodies` for the fixture.\n   - `AC013_BUDGET_*` constants at lines 149-150.\n6. `crates/fathomdb-engine/Cargo.toml` — confirm\n   `sqlite-vec = \"=0.1.7\"` pin. Pack 1 may optionally bump to\n   `0.1.9` for the constraint-column improvements — only if\n   needed; not required for `bit[N]`.\n\n## Step 0 — Draft the ADR\n\nBefore Pack 1 lands a single byte of code, draft an ADR:\n\n`dev/adr/ADR-0.7.0-vector-binary-quant.md` (or rename the\nexisting `ADR-0.7.0-text-query-latency-gates-revised.md` if it\nmakes more sense to bundle).\n\nThe ADR must cover:\n\n- Problem (AC-013 canonical-CI gap, root cause).\n- Decision: binary quantization + f32 rerank on `sqlite-vec`\n  0.1.7; metadata + partition_key on the same migration.\n- Alternatives considered (vectorlite, sqlite-vec ANN alpha,\n  Rust-side `usearch`, embedder change) — all rejected, with\n  reasons from the research doc.\n- Consequences: schema change, ingest cost, query-path\n  rewrite, recall floor as RED test, post-0.7.0 follow-ups.\n- Status: `draft, HITL-required` initially. Lock-flip is\n  orchestrator's; do not flip prematurely.\n\n## Pack 1 — schema migration + ingest double-write\n\nGoal: land the new schema and the new ingest path. **No reader\nbehavior change.** AC-013 / AC-019 still measure on the\nunindexed f32 path; their numbers stay at 2048/2327 until\nPack 2.\n\n### 1.1 — Schema migration\n\nModify `vector_default` (or add a sibling\n`vector_default_bin`). Decision criterion:\n\n- **Sibling column on the same vec0 table** — simpler\n  application code; sqlite-vec supports mixed `float[768]` +\n  `bit[768]` columns on the same vec0. **Default choice.**\n- **Sibling table** — only if the column-flavour hits a\n  vec0 limitation (e.g., metadata column count limit, which is\n  16 per\n  [sqlite-vec features](https://alexgarcia.xyz/blog/2024/sqlite-vec-metadata-release/index.html)).\n\nNew columns:\n\n- `embedding_bin bit[768]` — the load-bearing quantized\n  column. Built with `vec_quantize_binary(embedding)`.\n- `source_type TEXT` — **partition_key, locked HITL\n  2026-05-27**. Cardinality ~6 (email, article, paper, meeting,\n  note, todo). Maps to user-facing search-scope filters and\n  yields fast pre-filtered KNN under `WHERE source_type = ?`.\n  Existing chunk records have a vector kind via\n  `_fathomdb_vector_rows.kind` (verify exact column name when\n  reading lib.rs); map kind → source_type at write time\n  (deterministic 1:1 mapping for current kinds; the\n  source_type vocabulary is the authoritative set going\n  forward).\n- Additional metadata columns (non-partition): `kind` (kept\n  for backwards compat if it differs from source_type),\n  `created_at`, `tags`, `project_mentions`, etc. Per HITL\n  Q5: descriptive retrieval filters go in metadata columns +\n  WHERE predicates, not partition_keys. vec0 metadata column\n  limit is 16; budget the schema with headroom.\n\nMigration SQL: one-pass `INSERT ... SELECT\nvec_quantize_binary(embedding) FROM vector_default` for the\nexisting 1 M test corpus. Costs ~64 s on the dev box; well\ninside the workflow timeout.\n\n### 1.2 — Writer ingest double-write\n\nAt `_fathomdb_vector_rows` insert site (`lib.rs:2846` area):\n\n- After the f32 `embedding` insert, compute\n  `vec_quantize_binary(embedding)` and insert into the\n  `embedding_bin` column in the same transaction.\n- The bit column is non-nullable post-Pack 1 (every f32 row\n  has a bit row); enforce via NOT NULL or by post-write\n  migration.\n- Populate `kind` + `partition_key` from the existing chunk\n  record fields.\n- The writer transaction commits all columns atomically — no\n  separate commit for the bit column.\n\n### 1.3 — Pack 1 tests\n\n- **Migration round-trip test** — insert a known f32 vector,\n  verify the bit column contains the expected popcount\n  pattern (`vec_distance_hamming` returns 0 against itself\n  after binarization).\n- **Writer regression** — existing AC-012, AC-017, AC-018,\n  AC-020 tests continue to pass. Pack 1 changes schema but\n  not query semantics, so all should be GREEN.\n- **No AC-013 budget change yet** — AC-013 stays pinned at\n  the unindexed 50/200 budget (current `perf_gates.rs:149-150`)\n  and continues to fail at canonical-CI 1M scale until\n  Pack 2.\n\n### 1.4 — Pack 1 closure\n\nLand the schema + ingest changes as one or two commits on\n`main` (campaign convention from PCACHE2). No canonical-CI\ndispatch is required for Pack 1 — the schema change has no\nRED gate at canonical scale. Smoke test via dev-box AC-013 at\nN=10_000 to confirm the ingest double-write doesn't crash.\n\n## Pack 2 — query-path swap + RED tests\n\nGoal: switch the reader to bit-KNN → f32 rerank and pin the\nnew AC-013 budgets.\n\n### 2.1 — RED tests FIRST\n\nBefore the query rewrite, land:\n\n- **AC-013 latency budget re-pin** in\n  `tests/perf_gates.rs:149-150`:\n  - `AC013_BUDGET_P50 = Duration::from_millis(80);`\n  - `AC013_BUDGET_P99 = Duration::from_millis(300);`\n- **New AC recall-floor test** (e.g., `ac_NNN_recall_at_10`):\n  - Computes brute-force f32 ground truth at test-setup\n    (one pass through the existing f32 column, no\n    rerank).\n  - Runs the production search path, captures top-10 IDs\n    per query.\n  - Asserts `recall@10 ≥ 0.90` (HITL-locked floor).\n  - The ground-truth pass uses the *same* f32 column that\n    Pack 2 retains for rerank — single corpus, both jobs.\n\nBoth tests must FAIL at canonical-CI N=1M before the query\nrewrite lands. Dispatch the perf-canonical workflow with\n`targets=\"ac013 ac019\"` and the locked W4.1-stacked-O1 env\nknobs (see HITL doc) to confirm RED.\n\n### 2.2 — `read_search_in_tx` rewrite\n\nAt `lib.rs:2317-2323`, replace the single-phase f32 KNN with\ntwo-phase:\n\n```sql\n-- Phase 1: bit-KNN to top-K candidates (K=64 default)\nWITH candidates AS (\n  SELECT rowid, distance AS bit_distance\n  FROM vector_default\n  WHERE embedding_bin MATCH vec_quantize_binary(vec_f32(?1))\n  ORDER BY distance\n  LIMIT 64\n)\n-- Phase 2: f32 rerank on the candidate set\nSELECT c.rowid, vec_distance_l2(v.embedding, vec_f32(?1)) AS d\nFROM candidates c\nJOIN vector_default v USING (rowid)\nORDER BY d\nLIMIT 10\n```\n\n(Exact SQL TBD against sqlite-vec syntax — see\n[sqlite-vec API ref](https://deepwiki.com/asg017/sqlite-vec/3-api-reference)\nand the binary-quant guide cited in the research doc.)\n\nK=64 picked from the binary-quant literature (Cohere, Kyle\nHowells benches) for ≥ 95 % recall@10 at our scale. Make K a\nconstant / config knob so future tuning is cheap.\n\n### 2.3 — Pack 2 validation\n\n- Local dev-box smoke at N=10_000 — both tests pass.\n- Canonical-CI dispatch with the same lever stack:\n  - AC-013 GREEN at ≤ 80 / 300 ms.\n  - AC-019 GREEN (existing 10× bound; should improve\n    substantially).\n  - Recall@10 ≥ 0.90 against f32 ground truth.\n\n### 2.4 — Pack 2 closure\n\nOnce canonical-CI is GREEN, the AC-013 / AC-019 rows in the\nrevised-budgets ADR can be filled with the measurement\nnumbers + headroom (~10 %), and the ADR lock-flip can\nproceed.\n\n## Done = ?\n\nThis handoff closes when:\n\n- ADR drafted (`status: draft, HITL-required`).\n- Pack 1 lands; ingest double-writes; schema migration\n  documented in the ADR.\n- Pack 2 lands; both RED tests transition to GREEN at\n  canonical-CI; recall@10 ≥ 0.90.\n- HITL signs off on the AC-013 / AC-019 numeric budgets.\n- ADR `status: locked`; orchestrator commits the lock-flip.\n- `dev/notes/pcache2-followups.md` is updated to reference\n  this work as the AC-013/019 closure.\n- Per-slice closure JSONs land in `dev/plans/runs/`.\n\n## Out of scope\n\n- Vectorlite, sqlite-vec ANN alpha, usearch / instant-distance.\n  Tracked for post-0.7.0 in `dev/notes/pcache2-followups.md`.\n- Embedder change.\n- ANN graph index of any kind.\n- Multi-process / multi-DB testing (FathomDB's single-writer\n  contract is preserved as-is).\n- AC-017 / AC-018 changes (out of scope; existing budgets\n  hold).\n\n## Open items the implementing agent should escalate to HITL\n\n- If `vec_quantize_binary()` semantics differ from this\n  handoff's assumption (e.g., it requires normalized input\n  but `VaryingEmbedder` produces unnormalized vectors),\n  escalate before Pack 1 ingest changes.\n- If the metadata-column count (max 16 per vec0) is\n  insufficient for FathomDB's actual kind cardinality + future\n  schema needs, escalate before Pack 1 schema design.\n- If the recall floor at K=64 falls below 0.90 on the AC-013\n  fixture, escalate before Pack 2 GREEN-test commit. K may\n  need to rise to 128 or 256; document the choice.\n- If a future reviewer counts binary-quant as a second\n  architectural lever, escalate immediately — fallback is\n  to slip Pack 2 to 0.7.1.\n\n## Citations\n\n- Research: `dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md`.\n- HITL doc: `dev/plans/0.7.0-HITL-recommendations.md`.\n- PCACHE2 ADR (precedent for HITL-driven 0.7.0 architectural\n  lever): `dev/adr/ADR-0.7.0-ac020-architectural-lever.md`.\n- Budgets ADR (target for the post-Pack-2 lock-flip):\n  `dev/adr/ADR-0.7.0-text-query-latency-gates-revised.md`.\n- sqlite-vec binary quantization guide:\n  https://alexgarcia.xyz/sqlite-vec/guides/binary-quant.html\n- sqlite-vec API reference:\n  https://deepwiki.com/asg017/sqlite-vec/3-api-reference\n- sqlite-vec metadata + partition release:\n  https://alexgarcia.xyz/blog/2024/sqlite-vec-metadata-release/index.html\n- Kyle Howells binary-quant benchmark:\n  https://ikyle.me/blog/2025/binary-quantized-embeddings\n","numLines":312,"startLine":1,"totalLines":312}}}
