{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0187KgDckx3TGw3NJuwn2wWU","type":"tool_result","content":"265\t  always remediate.\n266\t\n267\t## 8. Closure output.json schema (per slice)\n268\t\n269\tImplementer writes this as part of the slice; orchestrator reads it\n270\tto drive the cherry-pick + plan-update step.\n271\t\n272\t```json\n273\t{\n274\t  \"phase\": \"<id>\",\n275\t  \"baseline_sha\": \"<sha branch was cut from>\",\n276\t  \"branch\": \"phase-<id>-<ts>\",\n277\t  \"head_sha\": \"<HEAD after final commit>\",\n278\t  \"commits\": [\"<sha>: <subject>\", \"...\"],\n279\t  \"findings_addressed\": [\"...\"],\n280\t  \"blockers_encountered\": [{\"id\": \"...\", \"description\": \"...\", \"resolution\": \"...\"}],\n281\t  \"additional_changes_made_in_scope\": [\"...\"],\n282\t  \"agent_verify_result\": \"pass | fail (+ tail)\",\n283\t  \"next_step_for_orchestrator\": \"...\"\n284\t}\n285\t```\n286\t\n287\tImplementer-side discipline: write the JSON last, after all commits.\n288\tImplementer may commit the JSON itself as a final docs commit OR\n289\tleave it untracked (orchestrator promotes via Write tool before\n290\tworktree removal — see § 11).\n291\t\n292\t## 9. Decision loop (per slice)\n293\t\n294\tAfter implementer returns:\n295\t\n296\t1. Read `dev/plans/runs/<phase>-output.json` (per § 8 schema).\n297\t2. Cherry-pick implementer commits from WT branch onto mainline\n298\t   release branch (per § 5).\n299\t3. Spawn codex reviewer on the WT branch HEAD (per § 3).\n300\t4. Promote codex verdict body from log to canonical\n301\t   `dev/plans/runs/<phase>-review-<rts>.md` (per § 4).\n302\t5. Decide:\n303\t   - **PASS** → close phase, advance.\n304\t   - **CONCERN (structural / prompt-induced)** → orchestrator\n305\t     override (per § 7), close phase.\n306\t   - **CONCERN (substantive) / BLOCK** → fix-1 remediation (per\n307\t     § 6), goto step 1.\n308\t6. Edit master plan (\"Immediate Next Slice\" section or equivalent):\n309\t   add `Phase <id> CLOSED` block, advance mainline pointer.\n310\t7. Commit plan + verdict + prompt files in single docs commit:\n311\t   `docs(<phase>): promote codex <verdict>; close Phase <id>;\n312\tadvance to <next>`.\n313\t8. After all sub-phases of a phase family close: worktree cleanup\n314\t   (per § 11).\n315\t\n316\t## 10. Hard rules summary\n317\t\n318\t1. Main thread orchestrates. No orchestrator subagent.\n319\t2. Bash to spawn `claude -p`. Never Agent tool.\n320\t3. PREAMBLE prepended via stdin. Always.\n321\t4. `--disallowedTools Task Agent` on every implementer spawn.\n322\t5. Codex reviewer is read-only. Always `--sandbox read-only`.\n323\t6. Verdict promoted by main thread (codex can't write).\n324\t7. Cherry-pick to mainline, never merge from WT branch."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"aa315b5f-03de-4674-91e7-1c237d33c95a","uuid":"cdb95e3a-3522-4552-955f-df5c7232e508","timestamp":"2026-05-27T13:12:06.762Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/fdb-0.7.0-PVQ-S0-20260527T130459Z/dev/design/orchestration.md","content":"  always remediate.\n\n## 8. Closure output.json schema (per slice)\n\nImplementer writes this as part of the slice; orchestrator reads it\nto drive the cherry-pick + plan-update step.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"phase\": \"<id>\",\n  \"baseline_sha\": \"<sha branch was cut from>\",\n  \"branch\": \"phase-<id>-<ts>\",\n  \"head_sha\": \"<HEAD after final commit>\",\n  \"commits\": [\"<sha>: <subject>\", \"...\"],\n  \"findings_addressed\": [\"...\"],\n  \"blockers_encountered\": [{\"id\": \"...\", \"description\": \"...\", \"resolution\": \"...\"}],\n  \"additional_changes_made_in_scope\": [\"...\"],\n  \"agent_verify_result\": \"pass | fail (+ tail)\",\n  \"next_step_for_orchestrator\": \"...\"\n}\n```\n\nImplementer-side discipline: write the JSON last, after all commits.\nImplementer may commit the JSON itself as a final docs commit OR\nleave it untracked (orchestrator promotes via Write tool before\nworktree removal — see § 11).\n\n## 9. Decision loop (per slice)\n\nAfter implementer returns:\n\n1. Read `dev/plans/runs/<phase>-output.json` (per § 8 schema).\n2. Cherry-pick implementer commits from WT branch onto mainline\n   release branch (per § 5).\n3. Spawn codex reviewer on the WT branch HEAD (per § 3).\n4. Promote codex verdict body from log to canonical\n   `dev/plans/runs/<phase>-review-<rts>.md` (per § 4).\n5. Decide:\n   - **PASS** → close phase, advance.\n   - **CONCERN (structural / prompt-induced)** → orchestrator\n     override (per § 7), close phase.\n   - **CONCERN (substantive) / BLOCK** → fix-1 remediation (per\n     § 6), goto step 1.\n6. Edit master plan (\"Immediate Next Slice\" section or equivalent):\n   add `Phase <id> CLOSED` block, advance mainline pointer.\n7. Commit plan + verdict + prompt files in single docs commit:\n   `docs(<phase>): promote codex <verdict>; close Phase <id>;\nadvance to <next>`.\n8. After all sub-phases of a phase family close: worktree cleanup\n   (per § 11).\n\n## 10. Hard rules summary\n\n1. Main thread orchestrates. No orchestrator subagent.\n2. Bash to spawn `claude -p`. Never Agent tool.\n3. PREAMBLE prepended via stdin. Always.\n4. `--disallowedTools Task Agent` on every implementer spawn.\n5. Codex reviewer is read-only. Always `--sandbox read-only`.\n6. Verdict promoted by main thread (codex can't write).\n7. Cherry-pick to mainline, never merge from WT branch.","numLines":60,"startLine":265,"totalLines":516}}}
